National Security Advisor Dr. Phil Gordon met with families of Israeli hostages held by Hamas terrorists in Gaza during his trip to Israel and the West Bank. He conveyed the unwavering support of President Biden, Vice President Harris, and the entire Biden-Harris Administration. Dr. Gordon assured the families that the administration will make every effort to secure the release of all hostages. He emphasized that the well-being of the hostages is a top priority in diplomatic discussions and reiterated the commitment to collaborate with Israel, Qatar, and Egypt to negotiate a new deal for their release.